Subsequently, I observed blotches appearing on my forehead and limbs, while perspiration streamed down my visage. She inhaled deeply several times, yet she was unable to maintain her breath. Fear engulfed me, leaving me uncertain of how to proceed. Out of nowhere, a voice echoed from the warehouse's far end. The manager had discovered my plight and was calling out to me. Clearly, someone had taken note of my condition and was verifying my well-being. Attempting to respond that I was in distress, I tried to yell back, however, my voice seemed to have vanished. As the manager drew closer, my surroundings began to fade to darkness. I felt myself starting to collapse, but fortunately, the manager was swift to catch me just as I nearly hit the floor. He escorted me to the staff area and seated me in a chair. He inquired about my state and what had transpired. Handing me a chilled glass of water, he advised me to rest. After a short while, the constriction in his chest subsided and he started to recover. It was revealed that I had experienced a panic attack, yet thanks to the manager's prompt action, I was pulled out of the ordeal. The ordeal was far from enjoyable, however, it could have had a more severe outcome. This incident taught me the importance of self-regulation and ensuring adequate rest and nutrition to prevent future episodes.
